	<preparation>Combine garlic, bouillon, 1/3 cup water, vinegar and soy sauce.  Add meat product.  Marinate at room temperature for 1 hour.  Simmer uncovered, 30 minutes and add pineapple, water chestnuts and onion.  Simmer 5 minutes.

Stir in pea pods, cook 5 minutes.  Soften cornstarch in 1 Tbsp water and stir into mixture.  Cool until thick and clear.  Add tomato, salt and pepper.  Serve with chow mein noodles or rice (end note: "Ala Bulgar wheat", yo)</preparation>
